oracle.apps.saf.ta.jaudit.model.facades
Interface ViolationReportFacade

All Known Implementing Classes:
ViolationReportFacadeImpl
public interface ViolationReportFacade

Audit violations must be reported through this facade.

JAudit violations in SAF must use this facade. It will handle exemption processing automatically. It supports built in violation message variants. Invoke the appropriate report message that corresponds to the message denoted in your RuleResources annotation. Various {code addX} convenience methods exist to provide values for message tokens. The token value in the RuleResources is the suffix of the {code addX} converted to camelCase.


For example a value placed in addAttrName will substitue attrName in the RuleResources message.
